## 3. Dark Mode — Class-Based Only (Critical)

This project uses **class-based dark mode** (`html.dark`) — NOT Tailwind's `dark:` prefix.

### Why `dark:` prefix is forbidden

Tailwind v4 `dark:` variants use `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` by default. Our backgrounds are controlled by the `html.dark` CSS class (set by the toggle button). Mixing both causes:
- Light background (class not set) + dark text (system media query fires) = invisible text on light card
- Exact scenario: OS is dark mode, user hasn't toggled site → `dark:text-amber-100` (cream) on cream card

### Rules

- **NEVER** use `dark:` Tailwind prefix in any JSX/TSX (`dark:text-*`, `dark:bg-*`, etc.)
- **ALWAYS** add dark mode overrides in `app/globals.css` under `html.dark .class-name { }`
- All text colour dark-mode overrides live in the `/* Dark mode text helpers */` section of `globals.css`
- When adding a new text colour class, add its `html.dark` override immediately

### Correct pattern

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — class-based only
<p className="text-amber-900">Reviewer Name</p>

// ❌ Wrong — dark: prefix conflicts with our toggle
<p className="text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-100">Reviewer Name</p>
```

```css
/* globals.css — add override here */
html.dark .text-amber-900 {
  color: #FDE68A; /* 9.1:1 contrast on dark card */
}
```

---

## 4. Glassmorphism — Required Properties

Every `.glass-*` utility must use CSS variables so both modes are covered:

```css
.glass-card {
  background: var(--glass-card-bg);      /* swaps via html.dark */
  backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
  border: 1px solid var(--glass-card-border);
  transition: background 0.35s ease, border-color 0.35s ease;
}
```

Never hardcode `rgba(255,255,255,…)` in glass utilities — use the CSS variables defined in `:root` / `html.dark`.

---

## 5. Checklist When Adding New UI

- [ ] Text colour meets ≥ 4.5:1 in **light mode** against the card/background
- [ ] Corresponding `html.dark` override exists in `globals.css` with ≥ 4.5:1 on dark surface
- [ ] No `dark:` Tailwind prefix used anywhere in the component
- [ ] Any new CSS glass utility uses CSS variables (not hardcoded colours)
- [ ] Muted / metadata text meets ≥ 4.5:1 even at reduced opacity
